HEADWORD: Amphiarthrosis
<hw>Am`phi*ar*thro"sis</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>'amfi`</grk> + <?/ a joining, <?/ a joint.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A form of articulation in which the bones are
connected by intervening substance admitting slight motion;
symphysis.</def>⟦br⟧
